Hexadecimal to Decimal: Use the Sum-of-Weights method with powers of 16.

Example: $$
\begin{aligned}
(1\text{A})_{16} &= (1 \times 16^1) + (10 \times 16^0) \\
&= 16 + 10 \\
&= (26)_{10}
\end{aligned}
$$

Example: 

$$
\begin{aligned}
(1\text{A}3)_{16} &= (1 \times 16^2) + (10 \times 16^1) + (3 \times 16^0) \\
&= 256 + 160 + 3 \\
&= \mathbf{419} \\
\text{Result: } &(1\text{A}3)_{16} = (419)_{10}
\end{aligned}
$$

Binary to Hex: 

Group the binary bits into sets of four (starting from the right). Replace each group with its hex equivalent.

    Example: $(10101111)_2$

$$
\begin{aligned}
&\underbrace{1010}_{\text{A}} \ \underbrace{1111}_{\text{F}} \\
\text{Result: } &(\text{AF})_{16}
\end{aligned}
$$
